(firstQuint)Clinical and Instrumental Evaluation of Swallowing in Children With Cerebral Palsy.

 Cross-sectional and quantitative study with sample consisted of 50 children with cerebral palsy.

 The data collection consisted in detection of the main dysphagic manifestations in different consistency of food and types of cerebral palsy.

